CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 30, 1960, pg. A11 reads: "Frogs' Chaperones - Some of the wives of the Frogs served as chaperones at the teenage dancing party given by the Frogs at the Loendi Club on Monday night. Seated, left to right; Mmes. C.C. Blow, Henry Smith Jr., Ed H. Hale and John Woodyear.  Standing: Mmes. Francis Farmer, Morris Fountain, Marian Wyatt, a guest from New York whose daughter attended the affair; Melvin Stockton, Harry G. Washington and Clarence Waters.  Not shown are Mmes. Roland Sawyer and Percy A. Garland. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of FROGS chaperones, from left, seated: Mrs. C.C. Blow, Mrs. Henry Smith Jr., Mrs. Ed H. Hale, and Mrs. John Woodyear; standing: Mrs. Francis Farmer, Miriam Sharpe Fountain, Mrs. Marian Wyatt, Lenora Stockton, Mrs. Harry G. Washington, and Eleanor Waters, gathered in Loendi Club for FROGS teenage dance party, another version
